{"key":"processedPost-6529507","value":{"id":6529507,"first":6528852,"last":6529844,"when":1170613165,"utime":"02/04/07 08:19 PM","content":"I see every reason not to do it.  You don't <u>adjust</u> the temperature in a fruiting chamber.  If there's even a degree or two difference in the inside and outside temperature, your tub will develop condensation, robbing the air inside of humidity.  Use separate tubs for each, or better yet, incubate on a shelf at room temperature and save the tubs for fruiting chambers.<br />RR","title":"Re: Fruiting and Incubating in same chamber- quick question"}}